  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Grangettes is a lively ski hotel with a great location in <a data-udi="umb://document/870730cefeb2441dab9ccfec19c2fe88" href="/{localLink:umb://document/870730cefeb2441dab9ccfec19c2fe88}" title="Meribel">Méribel</a>, the Chaudanne ski lift is just across the road giving you access to the fantastic <a data-udi="umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578" href="/{localLink:umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578}" title="Three Valleys Ski Area">Three Valleys Ski Area</a>. The hotel, including the restaurant and Jacks Après Ski Bar, is run by European Pubs, a company with 15 years’ experience in the ski hospitality industry, successfully operating restaurants and bars across the French Alps.</p>
<h2>Lively Après</h2>
<p>After a day of exploring the <a data-udi="umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578" href="/{localLink:umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578}" title="Three Valleys Ski Area">Three Valleys</a> there's no better place to be in town than Jacks Après Ski Bar, formally the Mèribar which is just below the hotel. Après ski with live music starts in the late afternoon and runs until 7:30-8pm, when the venue opens to serve delicious restaurant evening meals. Throughout the day soak up the winter sun on terrace and enjoy the village atmosphere. If you are looking for somewhere for lunch in the resort, food is served throughout the day.</p>
<h2>Great location</h2>
<p>This lively hotel has one of the best locations in Méribel, perfectly located just across the street from the main Chaudanne ski lifts and ski school meeting point. For the keen skiers and boarders, getting first lifts is really easy assuming you haven’t spent too long in the après bar the night before. The atmospheric heart of <a data-udi="umb://document/870730cefeb2441dab9ccfec19c2fe88" href="/{localLink:umb://document/870730cefeb2441dab9ccfec19c2fe88}" title="Meribel">Méribel’s</a> main centre with a variety of shops, bars and restaurants is right on your doorstep.</p>
<h2>Home comforts</h2>
<p>The Grangettes is a welcoming and vibrant hotel which is ideal for friends and families who want to be able to access this great ski area easily and return to chill in the lounge area or a bit of après.</p>
<p>The hotel is on a half board basis, which includes breakfast and a three course evening meal. Dinner is served in the hotel dining room for Grangettes guests only. You can also swap your evening meal for a 20 Euro credit to spend in the Jack's restaurant which must be used on the same day of the swap.</p>]]></description>
